  "title": "Event Executive (Exhibitor Acquisition)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Primary Function:</strong></p><p>To assist the department in account management, sales prospecting and business development of our exhibitions/conferences to customers; generate sponsorship revenue; and oversee the collective coordination of all event information and resources.</p><p><strong>Main Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>1. To execute sales and marketing strategies in acquiring potential leads. </p><p>2. To identify new markets and business opportunities through various means including cold calling to increase event sales.</p><p>3. To actively source and prospect clients for exhibitions.</p><p>4. To prepare exciting and creative proposals to attract new sponsors and other clients at all levels.</p><p>5. To provide customers with quotations and follow up promptly.</p><p>6. To maintain and develop excellent customer relationships with clients and continuously focus on improving customer satisfaction to create customer loyalty and deliver a positive event experience.</p><p>7. To provide accurate and timely information to relevant internal and external parties. </p><p>8. To assist in conducting market research, market monitoring and business development activities to enhance efficiency and performance of the sales department.</p><p>9. To gather market and customer information to stay relevant in the market</p><p>10. To represent the Company at trade exhibitions and events for the purpose of collecting qualified leads and pertinent sales information as well as keeping up with market trends</p><p>11. To plan, design and implement other revenue-generating ideas, e.g. show directories/issues/diaries/dailies, merchandising, business centre, polaroids, awards, competitions, postcards, hospitality suites, plastic/paper bags, daily bulletins/messages boards, electronic media, press conferences, printing etc.</p><p>12. To source for mailing lists and oversee databases of potential sellers and hosted/trade buyers.</p><p>13. To submit and update sales/project reports.</p><p>15. To assist in any other duties assigned from time to time.</p>",
